-- Japan, China, India, Malaysia, Taiwan: Asia Bond, Foreign Exchange Preview
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   L u i
-- 2010-10-20T22:57:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/japan-china-india-malaysia-taiwan-asia-bond-foreign-exchange-preview.html
The following events and economic
reports may influence trading in Asia’s local bonds and
currencies today. Bond yields and exchange rates are from the
previous trading session unless stated otherwise.  Japan: Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshito Sengoku will hold
media briefings at 11 a.m. and 4 p.m. in Tokyo.  The Ministry of Finance will release at 8:50 a.m. in Tokyo
its report on Japanese and foreign investment flows for domestic
and overseas securities during the week ended Oct. 15.  The Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry will release at
1:30 p.m. in Tokyo its all-industry activity index for August.
Japan’s all-industry activity index fell 0.4 percent in August
from July, when it rose 1 percent, according to a Bloomberg News
survey of economists.  The yield on the 0.8 percent government bond due September
2020 was at 0.890 percent, according to Japan Bond Trading Co.,
the nation’s largest interdealer debt broker.  The yen traded at 81.04 per dollar at 7:49 a.m. in Tokyo.  China: The government will release September’s consumer
price index and producer price index, as well as retail sales,
industrial production and fixed asset investment data. It will
also unveil gross domestic product growth for the third quarter.  Third quarter GDP likely grew 9.5 percent from the same
period last year, according to the median estimate in a
Bloomberg news survey. GDP expanded 10.3 percent in the second
quarter.  Consumer prices rose 3.6 percent in September from a year
ago, the fastest pace in nearly two years, a separate survey
showed. Industrial production expanded 14 percent last month
from a year earlier, another survey showed.  China Development Bank will sell 20 billion yuan ($3
billion) of 3-year bonds and 20 billion yuan of 10-year floating
notes.  The yield on the 2.53 percent note due June 2015 was 2.72
percent. The yuan was at 6.6505.  India: The Ministry of Commerce & Industry will release
wholesale price indexes, a measure of inflation, for the week
ended Oct. 9.  The yield on the 7.80 percent bond due May 2020 was 8.11
percent. The rupee was at 44.285.  Taiwan: The government will issue NT$25 billion ($810
million) of 364-day Treasury bills.  The yield on the 1.125 percent note due September 2020 was
1.23 percent, according to Gretai Securities Market, the
island’s biggest exchange for bonds. Taiwan’s dollar traded at
NT$30.93.  Malaysia: The government will issue 100 million ringgit
($32 million) of 364-day Islamic bills.  The yield on the 3.835 percent note due August 2015 was
3.32 percent, according to Bursa Malaysia. The ringgit traded at
3.1205 per dollar.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
 Patricia Lui  at   plui4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandy Hendry at   shendry@bloomberg.net  